  "prompt": "Is it possible to skip a grade in Italian high schools?",
  "response": "In Italy, skipping a grade (anticipare un anno scolastico) is possible, but it's not very common. Here are some key points:\n\n1. Conditions for skipping a grade:\n- Exceptional academic performance\n- Student demonstrates advanced knowledge and skills\n- Recommended by teachers\n- Approved by the school's faculty council\n\n2. Process:\n- Requires formal evaluation of the student's abilities\n- Must show readiness for more advanced curriculum\n- Usually requires passing special exams or assessments\n\n3. Limitations:\n- More challenging in the Italian school system compared to some other countries\n- Each case is evaluated individually\n- Not guaranteed, even with strong academic performance\n\n4. High school stages:\n- Most common in lower secondary school (scuola media)\n- Less frequent in liceo or other high school types\n\n5. Considerations:\n- Social and emotional maturity are also important factors\n- Psychological readiness is evaluated alongside academic performance\n\nWhile possible, skipping a grade is relatively rare in the Italian educational system and depends on multiple factors and individual school decisions.",
